      • insertIntoAssociatedTable

        public void insertIntoAssociatedTable​(Concept concept,
                                      Attribute attribute,
                                      AssociatedTableType associatedTableType,
                                      Context context)
        This method inserts all items in the given column into corresponding associated tables. Example:
        Consider a table of type MarkList with columns "Participant, Semester, Mark"
        It may be the attribute value of an individual "exam44".
        Each participant may now have an associated table "marks" with columns "Exam, Semester, Mark"
        The purpose of this method is now to turn each row, like for example "Tom, 3, 2.7" into a row "exam44, 3, 2.7" and add it to Tom's associated "marks"-table.
        Parameters:
        concept - a concept (like "exam44" in the example)
        attribute - an attribute (like "marks" in the example)
        associatedTableType - the corresponding associated table type ("Exam, Semester, Mark", in the example)
        context - the corresponding context.
